# Next.js Pages and Routing Structure

## Public Pages
- **Home**: [pages/index.tsx](mdc:pages/index.tsx) - Main landing page with hero section
- **Menu**: [pages/menu.tsx](mdc:pages/menu.tsx) - Restaurant menu display
- **About**: [pages/about.tsx](mdc:pages/about.tsx) - Restaurant information
- **Contact**: [pages/contact.tsx](mdc:pages/contact.tsx) - Contact form and information
- **Gallery**: [pages/gallery.tsx](mdc:pages/gallery.tsx) - Photo gallery
- **Events**: [pages/events.tsx](mdc:pages/events.tsx) - Special events page
- **Login**: [pages/login.tsx](mdc:pages/login.tsx) - Authentication page

## Admin Pages
- **Admin Dashboard**: [pages/admin.tsx](mdc:pages/admin.tsx) - Admin entry point
- **Admin Routes**: [pages/admin/](mdc:pages/admin) - Protected admin functionality

## Special Pages
- **404 Error**: [pages/404.tsx](mdc:pages/404.tsx) - Custom error page
- **Document**: [pages/_document.tsx](mdc:pages/_document.tsx) - HTML document wrapper
- **App**: [pages/_app.tsx](mdc:pages/_app.tsx) - App-level configuration

## API Routes
- **Authentication**: [pages/api/auth/](mdc:pages/api/auth) - NextAuth.js endpoints
- **API Routes**: [pages/api/](mdc:pages/api) - Backend API endpoints

## Routing Notes
- Uses Next.js file-based routing
- Admin routes are protected with authentication middleware
- API routes handle backend functionality and database operations
